article.headline: Hartford 69, Fairleigh Dickinson 59
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Yolonzo Moore II scored 27 points, including 13 of 14 from the free-throw line, to lead Hartford to a 69-59 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson in a nonconference game Sunday. Moore, a sophomore guard, played the entire 40 minutes and surpassed his previous career high by 10 points. The Hawks (5-4) trailed 34-30 at halftime and 38-30 early in the second half before scoring the next 18 points. Moore's 3-pointer gave them a 41-38 lead with 13:47 remaining and they never trailed again. Taylor Dyson scored the next three baskets for Hartford, one of them a 3-pointer, to make it 48-38. Moore was perfect on 10 free throws in the final 1:26. He also had eight rebounds and three steals. Kinu Rochford and Lonnie Robinson scored 13 points apiece for the Knights (4-5), and Rochford also had nine rebounds. Sekou Harris added 11 points.
